{
  "texts": [
    "For uniformly sum of the two scores, which considers Has_Answer and LLM_Prefer together, does not improve the R@k, but it significantly improves the answering accuracy.",
    "This is because Has_Answer ensures documents contain factual information, andLLM_Prefer selects documents which are useful to the LLM.",
    "Combining the two labels can provide documents that contain factual information and are LLMs preferred, which improve the answering accuracy.",
    "We can see from Figure 10 that our proposed bi-label scorer improves the accuracy by 2.5% in TriviaQA, 0.4% in NQ and 1.7% in PopQA compared with the similarity-based retriever, showing the effectiveness of our method.",
    "Top-5 Top-10 Top-20 Top-50 50 60 70 80 90 100 Recall@K Contriever One Label (Has_Answer) One Label (LLM_Prefer) Bi-Label Fig. 9."
  ]
}